I'll start off by saying I went there at 9pm, an hour before closing time. I didn't think that it was too late for an establishment to serve their full menu, but apparently they are of a different opinion at Snappy's.  I wanted to try it and the lady told my friend and I that sandwiches and wraps were no longer available at the time; only deep fried things.  I thought this was weird but I still wanted to try them out.  My friend got chicken wings and I got an assortment of catfish, shimp, and something else.  My friend like the wings. I thought the shrimp and fish was okay. I mean, it was all just deep fried stuff. Nothing special. I don't think I'll be coming back unless I am overcome by laziness and hunger as I pass by.

I wanted to try a new place that specializes in serving high quality shrimp.  I found this place on Google Maps and was extremely excited based on the reviews.  I walked up to the counter with that excitement only to be shot down by the very blah cashier.  I still showed my enthusiasm and told him that I found their restaurant online and wanted to give it a try.  He didn't thank me or acknowledge my comment.  He asked what I wanted to order.  My first instinct was to walk out, but I drove an hour from the Northwest Suburbs.  Upon receiving my order, the cook gave me the same blah attitude and pretty much handed me my order and said nothing...not..."Here you go", "Thank you" or "Have a good day".  The food was fantastic, but the service was very mediocre.  Businesses need to realize the importance of customer service.  Customers are the lifeline for any business. Good customer service is essential and will assist in creating new customers, keeping loyal customers, and developing referrals for future customers.  Will I visit again...not sure.  I have no motivation to drive an hour only to be treated as if my business is not important or appreciated.  If I received both a good product AND good customer service, my answer would be definitely!  It would be worth the drive.

The Crab Cake sandwich is "Da Bomb"! Pair it with their awesome $2.50 meal upgrade (side+soda) and you've got a deal that can't be beat. The staff is always friendly and I can't think of one bad item on the menu. Snappy's is the spot!

Oh My, 1/2 lb. of catfish, a side of fries, a side of potato salad, a side of clam strips, a side of hush puppies, and two pops - $11!  Amazing.  This quaint little place is a great spot if your in the mood for fried foods - and who isn't?  It's located right by the Irving Park brown line so you don't have to complain of it being too far to walk to or something like that.   There's limited seating,  but it's mostly a take-out place so don't start worrying if you plan to stay to eat.  Everything was great.  The serving of catfish was more than plenty - I basically paid $5.50 for dinner since my friend and I decided to share.  I only wish this place was open really late - I wouldn't mind getting some chicken strips as a drunk food.
